<span class="displaytext"><b> <em>"and it is the strength of this nation's families that ultimately determines america's strength in the family of nations. that is why i believe that the most important work for the future of america is the work that goes on within the four walls of the american home."</em> â€“ governor (candidate last)</b> (gov. (candidate full), remarks at the family research council, washington, d.c., 10/19/07) <p><u> <b>governor (candidate last)'s conservative plan to strengthen and empower florida families:</b> </u> </p><p><b>today, in florida, governor (candidate full) discussed his conservative plan to strengthen families in florida.</b> there is much our nation can do to strengthen families because our future is determined not just by heads of state but also by heads of households. as president, governor (candidate last) will ensure that washington stands alongside parents who are building stronger families. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- governor (candidate last) believes our nation and florida are stronger when we have stronger families.</b> the source of most of society's social problems can be traced to a breakdown of the family. florida is wealthier, healthier and stronger when it has strong families. </p></blockquote> <p><b> <u>wall #1: championing marriage:</u> </b> </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) will champion a federal marriage amendment to protect marriage as the union of a man and a woman.</b> governor (candidate last) believes marriage is primarily about the development and nurturing of children. every child deserves a mother and a father. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p>- <b>governor (candidate last) is <u>the only</u> major (PARTY NAME) candidate who supports a federal amendment because it is the only way to truly protect marriage.</b> </p></blockquote> <p><b>governor (candidate last) will realign government incentives to encourage marriage, not penalize it.</b> today, a single mother with child care who marries the father of her child can lose as much as $6,000 a year in government benefits. their combined incomes can disqualify them for medicaid, housing vouchers, food stamps, and welfare. it is time to make fathers responsible for their child's health and care. furthermore, we need to end the tax penalty on married couples. </p><p><b> <u>wall #2: protecting our children:</u> </b> </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) will fight the modern plague of internet pornography.</b> we must clean up the culture that surrounds our children in florida and across the country. as president, governor (candidate last) will work to ensure that every home computer has an easy to engage pornography filter so that parents can protect their children. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p>- <b>governor (candidate last) has proposed a new "one strike, you're ours" law toughening sentences against online predators.</b> predators who use the internet to sexually assault children will be subject to a new "one strike, you're ours" law of imposing long prison sentences followed by lifetime gps tracking. according to the national center for missing and exploited children, as of april 2007, there were nearly 42,000 convicted sex offenders in florida. governor (candidate last)'s "one strike, you're ours" law follows the lead of florida in cracking down on people who prey on children. </p></blockquote> <p><b>governor (candidate last) will take the campaign against drugs to a new level.</b> we can do a better job educating our kids on the perils of drug use. parents may be the best anti-drug there is. </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) will work to better schools and better education for our children.</b> governor (candidate last) believes in school choice and that every child should have an equal opportunity to have a good education. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- for parents home-schooling their children, governor (candidate last) proposes a federal tax credit to help defray expenses.</b> according to the florida department of education, more than 55,000 students in approximately 37,000 families are in home education programs in the state. </p><p><b>- governor (candidate last) will help florida parents save for their children's college education.</b> he has proposed a middle-class tax-free savings program for every florida family earning $200,000 a year or less. under his plan, the tax rate on interest, dividends and capital gains will be zero. </p></blockquote> <p><b> <u>wall #3: strengthening and empowering families: <br/></u> </b> <br/> <b>governor (candidate last) will ensure that families in florida have health insurance.</b> using proven, free-market principles, governor (candidate last)'s plan will ensure every citizen has health insurance, without new taxes, a government-run hillarycare style system or socialized medicine. in massachusetts, governor (candidate last) put conservative principles to work and the number of uninsured has been cut in half. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- in florida, 21 percent of the population is uninsured.</b> more than 3.7 million people are uninsured. for those with insurance, the average annual individual health insurance premium is $2,539. in 2004 alone, more than $95.2 billion was spent on health care by people in new hampshire. </p><p><b>- <a href="http://www.(candidate full).com/news/photo-albums/health_care_briefing">click here</a> to view governor (candidate last)'s powerpoint presentation.</b> </p></blockquote> <p><b>governor (candidate last) will strengthen families by lowering taxes.</b> governor (candidate last) has proposed a detailed conservative blueprint to lower taxes that includes making the bush tax cuts permanent, rolling back tax rates across the board for all americans, eliminating the death tax, eliminating taxes on the savings of middle-income americans, opposing social security tax increases, making medical expenses tax deductible and making our corporate tax rate more competitive with the rest of the world. </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) will convene a white house summit on strengthening families.</b> this white house summit will be a springboard to develop new initiatives to strengthen families across the country. </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) will reinstate the family impact statement.</b> to keep government from doing things that hurt and weaken families, president ronald reagan issued an executive order requiring that new government policies and programs be subject to the family impact statement. however, president (candidate last) rescinded this executive order. governor (candidate last) will reinstate the family impact statement and initiate an audit of all current programs and policies which may negatively impact families. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- governor (candidate last) will support the rights of florida parents who are not always consulted about decisions affecting their children.</b> the work of being a parent is hard enough without the government making it harder. </p></blockquote> <p><b>governor (candidate last) will defend our religious heritage.</b> as president, governor (candidate last) will ensure that his attorney general defends the free exercise of religion. the united states is a nation under god and should remain that way. </p><p><b>as president, governor (candidate last) will lead by example.</b> the first family represents america to the world and represents america to our children and grandchildren. as president, governor (candidate last)'s family will live up to a higher standard and always try to make the american people proud. </p><p><b> <u>wall #4: promoting a culture of life:</u> </b> </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) will be a pro-life president.</b> governor (candidate last) will appoint and fight for judges who follow the law and constitution, who understand judicial restraint and will not legislate from the bench. as president, governor (candidate last) will promote pro-life polices. he will oppose taxpayer-funded abortion, partial-birth abortion, abortion in military clinics and funding of abortion in international aid programs. he will work to ban embryonic cloning. he will work to increase adoptions by making the adoption tax credit permanent and raising awareness about embryonic adoption, or snowflake babies. </p><p><b> <u>read governor (candidate last)'s full <em>strategy for a stronger america</em>:</u> </b> </p><p>to read more about governor (candidate last)'s agenda to change washington, please click on the <em> <a href="http://www.(candidate full).com/issue-watch/strategy">strategy for a stronger america</a> </em> , a compilation of his policy proposals for conservative change and to meet the new generation of challenges confronting our nation. since january 2007, governor (candidate last) has outlined more than 50 different policy proposals. from defeating violent jihadists to protecting traditional values, governor (candidate last) believes we can build a stronger america by taking washington apart and putting it back together based on conservative principles that strengthen our national defense, our economy and our families.</p></span>



